    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for LawDog (Team 7641) is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 76.47. He faces Martinez, who carries a shaky 4.59 xERA, allowing **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** to capitalize on a massive SP skill advantage and a favorable #3 hole placement. Close behind is **Bryson Stott** (72.10), who benefits from a prime matchup against Mahle (4.62 xERA). Despite the \"Elite Catcher\" sprint speed penalty\u2014a recurring theme for our baserunning-conscious strategy\u2014the positive platoon splits and park factors make **Bryson Stott** an essential start. We also see high value from **Gleyber Torres** (67.46), whose BvP metrics (25 PA) and favorable encounter with the lefty P\u00e9rez create one of the most reliable floor-ceiling profiles in today's rotation.\n\nThe tightest decision on the bench involved **Masyn Winn**, whose score of 44.46 fell just short of our threshold for active roster consideration. While **Masyn Winn** possesses the sprint speed we covet, the combination of an elite catcher\u2019s pop time and Ashcraft\u2019s effective pitch mix suppressed his projected efficiency. Consequently, we are prioritizing **Jeremiah Jackson** (55.92) and **Yainer Diaz** (61.21), both of whom benefit significantly from park adjustments. **Taylor Ward** and **Will Smith** are also strong plays today, with **Taylor Ward** capitalizing on an elite park factor and **Will Smith** providing steady, high-xwOBA output against Janson Junk.\n\nRisks today are concentrated in our outfield and catcher slots. **Cal Raleigh** (49.56) is a marginal start, as Ryan\u2019s 3.32 xERA poses a legitimate threat to his daily efficiency, and **Tyler Freeman** (45.44) faces an uphill battle against Burns, whose 2.76 xERA makes him the most dangerous arm on our opposing docket. While **Daulton Varsho** and **Gavin Sheets** round out the active roster, they remain sensitive to platoon volatility. We are closely monitoring weather reports, but as of now, the primary concern remains the high-strikeout potential of the pitchers facing **Tyler Freeman** and **Cal Raleigh**, which could depress their contributions to our AVG and RBI categories.",
